race.comment: MISS DECEIVER (8) will be strongly fancied to get off the mark here. Has placed two of three runs, both in rain-affected going, and has been racing in far richer maidens. Gets her chance to open winning account. BELLABAMA (5) had just one run in her first campaign in rich open two-year-old class at Swan Hill when ran on well to finish fourth. Resumes in easier and has been jumping out well. Expected to measure up. FLYING DONE (1) was safely held on debut then ran a much better race last time, hitting the line hard for sixth but beaten just a length. Heading the right way and should be winding up late. The race drops right away beyond those three to have raced. PANDA ALERT (3) is a well-educated three-year-old gelding by Ocean Park out of High Vogue who makes debut. Has had six trials in total but four more recently preparing for debut so should be ready to show something. COCKTAIL LADY (6) is another well-educated first starter from a good family. Nice draw and worth watching.
